==English==
===Etymology===
From the Greek [[ἑστία]], meaning [[hearth]], [[house]], [[home]], and [[family]]. 

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
{{wikipedia}}
# {{greekmyth}} virgin goddess of the [[hearth]] fire, and therefore [[domestic]] life; sister to [[Zeus]], oldest daughter of [[Rhea]] and [[Cronos]].

